  "footnotes": [
    "The Inca Empire (Tawantinsuyu, 1438–1533) stretched 4,000 km along the Andes — the largest pre-Columbian American empire",
    "Spanish conquest: Pizarro defeated the Inca (1533); colonial viceroyalties lasted ~300 years",
    "Simón Bolívar and José de San Martín led South American independence movements (1810s–1820s)",
    "Gran Colombia (1819–1831) united present-day Colombia, Venezuela, Ecuador, and Panama before dissolving",
    "Brazil uniquely transitioned from colony to empire (1822) under the Portuguese royal house, before becoming a republic in 1889"
